  "A car (1200 kg) drives at 20 m/s around a banked curve (bank angle 15°, radius 80 m). What friction force is needed if the speed exceeds the design speed? (g = 10 m/s²)": "",
  "Friction force ≈ 2,832 N directed down the incline": "",
  "Friction force ≈ 2,832 N directed up the incline": "",
  "No friction is needed": "",
  "Friction force ≈ 2,880 N directed up the incline (toward center)": "",
  "Design speed: v_d = sqrt(rg tanθ) = sqrt(80(10)(0.268)) = sqrt(214) ≈ 14.6 m/s. Since 20 > 14.6, friction acts up the incline. The centripetal force needed is mv²/r = 1200(400)/80 = 6000 N. N sin15° + f cos15° = 6000 and N cos15° - f sin15° = mg = 12000. Solving gives f ≈ 2880 N.": "",
